Has a Relationship:

A way to combine simpler classes to build more complex ones.
(One class depends on another class)

Eg : Combine small classes like wheel,engine to make a complex class Car

TYPES:

1.Composition (Strong Bond)

- The contained object cannot exist without the owning object. If the main object is destroyed, the inner object is also destroyed.

Eg.A House has a Room. If you demolish the house, the room ceases to exist.

2.Aggregation (Weak Bond)

- The contained object can exist independently of the owning object. If the main object is destroyed, the inner object survives.

Eg : A Department has a Professor. If the department closes down, the professor still exists and can join another department
